node.text:
Marine Harvest is perfect for anyone who enjoys delicious and convenient seafood! Products are high quality, healthy, and affordable foods to bring into your home. They are also perfect for busy parents who prefer homemade meals that are better than fast food for their kids. I used their Atlantic Salmon Poppers to make this Dynamite Salmon Poppers. Makes life a whole lot easier. They are available at @target Superstores and soon on @amazonfresh.

#MarineHarvest #MOWI #YummyFish #FishBites #Target #AmazonFresh

🔹DYNAMITE SAUCE🔹

1/2 cup mayo (or light mayo, can reduce to 1/3 cup)
1/2 cup sweet & chili sauce
1 tsp vinegar
2 tbsps ketchup
1/2 tsp black pepper
1 tbsp honey
3 tbsps sriracha sauce

node.title: Make meal time exciting with @marineharvest_usa frozen fish line

node.text:
Quick, easy, and absolutely flavorful, this healthy chipotle shrimp bowl is so irresistible, that you’ll want to make it time and time again. The shrimp bowl is so easy to customize and you can make the bowl in less than 30 minutes. It even works as a meal-prep as well if you want to make this ahead of time for lunch at work!

Grab the full recipe from the link in my  bio @cookinwithmima

https://www.cookinwithmima.com/healthy-chipotle-shrimp-bowl/

This crispy Mongolian Chicken is fast, easy, and only takes 35 minutes to make! This chicken recipe is packed with flavor, sweet but spicy, and tastes just like what you’d get at takeout; your family will finish every last bite.

Grab the full recipe from the link in my bio @cookinwithmima

https://www.cookinwithmima.com/mongolian-chicken/

node.text:
Quick and easy, this Cheesy Chicken Margherita Skillet is the perfect weeknight dinner as it tastes less than an hour to put together. This one pan chicken margherita meal is made with juicy chicken then topped with all your favorite toppings of a margherita pizza like ​​melty mozzarella cheese, pesto, and basil.

Grab the full step-by-step recipe from the link in my bio.

https://www.cookinwithmima.com/chicken-margherita-skillet/

node.text:
The weather is still in the high 90’s -100’s  here in Texas so summer isn’t quite over yet. This Watermelon Cucumber Feta Salad is the perfect salad for those hot days. So simple, delicious, and refreshing, you’ll want to make this all the time! It’s perfect for BBQs, picnics, or just an easy and light weeknight meal. Sweet but salty, you won’t be able to get enough of this salad!

Grab the recipe from the link in my bio @cookinwithmima

https://www.cookinwithmima.com/watermelon-cucumber-feta-salad/

node.text:
Simple to make and loaded with flavor, these Air Fryer Crispy Chicken Strips are super addictive. Made with an easy coating, these little lovelies are juicy on the inside and delightfully crunchy on the exterior – plus there’s a delicious homemade sauce too – win, win!

Grab the full recipe from the link in my bio @cookinwithmima

https://www.cookinwithmima.com/crispy-air-fryer-chicken-strips/

node.text:
Made with all of the favors of my go-to dip, this Spinach Artichoke Chicken is so delicious and easy to make. It’s made with juicy chicken breasts that are seared to golden perfection then topped with a creamy sauce with artichokes and spinach. It’s absolutely irresistible!

Grab the full step by step recipe from the link in my bio.

https://www.cookinwithmima.com/creamy-spinach-artichoke-chicken/

A simple and filling Grilled Beef Kofta recipe that’s ideal for entertaining or for a weeknight dinner. It’s full of flavor and can be enjoyed on its own or paired with rice pilaf, served with pita bread, tzatziki, or homemade hummus. It is so easy to make and your whole family will love it.

Grab the full recipe from my blog. Link in my bio @cookinwithmima

This simple cajun chicken pasta is so creamy and packed with flavor. It’s the perfect weeknight dinner as it comes together so quickly with only a handful of ingredients. Your family will love this as it’s the perfect blend of smoky and spicy flavors that is so addictive.

Grab the full recipe from the link in my bio @cookinwithmima
